cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in computer vision tasks, specifically in the domains of Cityscapes and GTA5. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the integration of Instance Normalization (IN) and Batch Normalization (BN) as building blocks, which relates to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of advanced deep architectures such as DenseNet, ResNet, ResNeXt, and SENet, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses domain adaptation methods, which relates to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
